<abstract>&lt;p&gt;[Excerpt] Large-scale changes caused by globalisation are making industrial relations more, rather than less important in Europe, according to a new European Commission report. This report highlights a growing trend towards company level negotiations, with workers&#39; principal concern being job security, rather than short term financial gain.&lt;/p&gt;</abstract>
